# .null Portal — environment
#
# ── Mainnet RPC (REQUIRED for the marketplace + "My Names" to work) ──────────────
# Those two features use getProgramAccounts (a program scan). EVERY keyless public
# mainnet RPC blocks gPA from a browser origin — measured: publicnode 504-times-out,
# api.mainnet-beta returns 403 "Access forbidden", ankr/drpc/omniatech 403/CORS/free-
# tier-disabled. So WITHOUT a dedicated endpoint the marketplace shows "MARKETPLACE RPC
# UNAVAILABLE" and My-Names can't load. Set this to a Helius / Triton / QuickNode URL
# (all have a free tier that allows gPA + browser CORS). Helius free tier = ~2 min to set up.
NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL_MAINNET=https://mainnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=YOUR_KEY

# ── Devnet RPC (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# api.devnet.solana.com DOES allow browser gPA, so devnet works keyless. Override only
# if you want a faster/dedicated devnet endpoint.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL_DEVNET=

# ── Legacy single override (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used as the mainnet fallback if NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL_MAINNET is unset, and as the
# default for cheap single-account reads (register/search availability), where the
# keyless publicnode default is fast and fine.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=

# NOTE: all of these are PUBLIC (NEXT_PUBLIC_) — they ship in the browser bundle.
# Never put a secret you don't want exposed here. If your provider key must stay
# private, front it with a proxy and point the URL at the proxy.
